<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>REACH Lab — University of Notre Dame</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --navy:   #0C1F3F;
      --gold:   #C99700;
      --gold-lt:#F0C840;
      --cream:  #FAF8F3;
      --stone:  #E8E4DB;
      --text:   #1A1A2E;
      --muted:  #5A6070;
      --accent: #2E6DAD;
    }

    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
      background: var(--cream);
      color: var(--text);
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    /* ── NAV ── */
    nav {
      position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 100;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
      padding: 0 48px; height: 64px;
      background: rgba(12,31,63,0.97);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(201,151,0,0.25);
    }
    .nav-logo {
      font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
      color: var(--gold-lt); font-size: 1.25rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-decoration: none;
    }
    .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 36px; list-style: none; }
    .nav-links a {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--gold-lt); }

    /* ── HERO ── */
    #hero {
      min-height: 100vh; background: var(--navy);
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      align-items: center; padding: 120px 80px 80px;
      position: relative; overflow: hidden;
    }
    #hero::before {
      content: ''; position: absolute; top: -180px; right: -180px;
      width: 700px; height: 700px; border-radius: 50%;
      border: 1px solid rgba(201,151,0,0.08); pointer-events: none;
    }
    #hero::after {
      content: ''; position: absolute; top: -80px; right: -80px;
      width: 500px; height: 500px; border-radius: 50%;
      border: 1px solid rgba(201,151,0,0.13); pointer-events: none;
    }
    .hero-text { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
    .hero-label {
      font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 20px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    }
    .hero-label::before { content: ''; display: inline-block; width: 32px; height: 1px; background: var(--gold); }
    .hero-acronym {
      font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
      font-size: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
      line-height: 1.1; color: var(--gold-lt); margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .hero-mission {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 500px;
      font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px;
      font-style: italic;
      border-left: 2px solid var(--gold);
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    .hero-sub {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); max-width: 480px;
      font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 44px;
    }
    .hero-cta {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
      background: var(--gold); color: var(--navy);
      padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: none;
      transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
    }
    .hero-cta:hover { background: var(--gold-lt); transform: translateY(-2px); }
    .hero-cta-ghost {
      display: inline-flex;
      border: 1px solid rgba(201,151,0,0.4); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
      padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: none;
      margin-left: 16px; transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
    }
    .hero-cta-ghost:hover { border-color: var(--gold); color: var(--gold-lt); }
    .hero-photos {
      padding-left: 60px; position: relative; z-index: 1;
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: 230px 230px; gap: 8px;
    }
    .hero-photos img {
      width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block;
      filter: brightness(0.8) saturate(0.85); transition: filter 0.4s;
    }
    .hero-photos img:hover { filter: brightness(1) saturate(1.1); }
    .hero-photos .tall { grid-row: span 2; }

    /* ── SECTION SHELL ── */
    section { padding: 100px 80px; }
    .section-label {
      font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 12px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    }
    .section-label::before { content: ''; display: inline-block; width: 24px; height: 1px; background: var(--gold); }
    h2 {
      font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem);
      color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 48px; line-height: 1.2;
    }

    /* ── ABOUT ── */
    #about { background: var(--cream); }
    .about-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 320px 1fr; gap: 72px; align-items: start; }

    .about-card { position: relative; }
    .about-card::after {
      content: ''; position: absolute; bottom: -6px; right: -6px;
      width: 100%; height: calc(100% - 0px); border: 1px solid var(--gold); pointer-events: none;
      top: 0;
    }
    .about-photo {
      width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 3/4; object-fit: cover; display: block;
      object-position: center top;
    }
    .about-card-info { background: var(--navy); padding: 24px 28px; }
    .about-name { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--gold-lt); margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .about-title-card { font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.7; }

    .about-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }

    /* Mission callout */
    .mission-block {
      background: var(--navy);
      padding: 32px 36px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
      position: relative;
    }
    .mission-block::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0;
      width: 3px; background: var(--gold);
    }
    .mission-label {
      font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .mission-text {
      font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
      font-size: 1.05rem; color: #fff;
      line-height: 1.7; font-style: italic;
    }

    .about-body p { margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.85; }
    .about-body p:first-of-type { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text); }

    /* Expertise pills */
    .expertise-grid {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 10px; margin-top: 28px;
    }
    .expertise-item {
      display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--stone);
      transition: border-color 0.2s;
    }
    .expertise-item:hover { border-color: var(--gold); }
    .expertise-dot {
      width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--gold); flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 7px;
    }
    .expertise-text { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
    .expertise-text strong { display: block; color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.8rem; margin-bottom: 2px; font-weight: 500; }

    /* Approach section — dark band */
    #approach {
      background: var(--navy); padding: 80px;
    }
    #approach h2 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 40px; }
    #approach .section-label { color: var(--gold); }
    .approach-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
    .approach-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.9; }
    .approach-text p { margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .approach-text strong { color: var(--gold-lt); font-weight: 500; }
    .approach-methods { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
    .method-row {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      border-left: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
    }
    .method-row:hover { border-color: var(--gold); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
    .method-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .method-label {
      font-size: 0.88rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
      font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .method-sub { font-size: 0.78rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35); margin-top: 2px; }

    /* ── FIELDWORK PHOTO STRIP ── */
    #fieldwork { background: var(--navy); padding: 0; overflow: hidden; }
    .photo-strip { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1.2fr 1.2fr 1.5fr; height: 380px; }
    .strip-photo { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
    .strip-photo img {
      width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block;
      transition: transform 0.5s ease, filter 0.3s;
      filter: brightness(0.7) saturate(0.85);
    }
    .strip-photo:hover img { transform: scale(1.05); filter: brightness(0.9) saturate(1.1); }
    .strip-caption {
      position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
      padding: 40px 18px 16px;
      background: linear-gradient(transparent, rgba(0,0,0,0.75));
      font-size: 0.71rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
      letter-spacing: 0.05em; font-style: italic;
    }

    /* ── RESEARCH ── */
    #research { background: var(--stone); }
    .research-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 2px; }
    .research-card {
      background: #fff; padding: 40px 32px;
      border-top: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
    }
    .research-card:hover { border-color: var(--gold); box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(12,31,63,0.08); }
    .research-icon { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 20px; display: block; }
    .research-card h3 { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .research-card p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.75; }

    /* ── PUBLICATIONS ── */
    #publications { background: var(--cream); }
    .pub-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    .pub-item {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 48px 1fr auto;
      gap: 24px; align-items: start;
      padding: 32px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(12,31,63,0.1);
    }
    .pub-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid rgba(12,31,63,0.1); }
    .pub-year { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--gold); padding-top: 3px; }
    .pub-title { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--navy); font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 6px; line-height: 1.5; }
    .pub-meta { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; }
    .pub-tag {
      font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 4px 10px; background: var(--navy); color: var(--gold-lt);
      white-space: nowrap; align-self: center;
    }
    .pub-highlight { background: rgba(12,31,63,0.03); }
    .pub-highlight .pub-title a {
      color: var(--navy); text-decoration: none;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .pub-highlight .pub-title a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
    .pub-highlight .pub-title { font-size: 1rem; }
    .pub-highlight .pub-tag {
      background: var(--gold); color: var(--navy); font-weight: 500;
    }
    .pub-note {
      font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 32px;
      padding: 20px 24px; border-left: 2px solid var(--gold);
      background: rgba(12,31,63,0.03);
    }

    /* ── CONTACT ── */
    #contact { background: var(--navy); }
    #contact h2 { color: #fff; }
    #contact .section-label { color: var(--gold); }
    .contact-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 80px; align-items: start; }
    .contact-block p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 36px; }
    .contact-detail { display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start; margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .contact-detail-icon {
      width: 36px; height: 36px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      font-size: 0.9rem; flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .contact-detail-text { font-size: 0.9rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); line-height: 1.6; }
    .contact-detail-text strong { color: var(--gold); display: block; font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 2px; font-weight: 500; }
    .contact-detail-text a { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); text-decoration: none; }
    .contact-detail-text a:hover { color: var(--gold-lt); }
    .contact-form { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
    .form-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }
    .contact-form input, .contact-form textarea {
      width: 100%; padding: 14px 18px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
      color: #fff;
      font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 0.9rem;
      outline: none; transition: border-color 0.2s;
    }
    .contact-form input:focus, .contact-form textarea:focus { border-color: var(--gold); }
    .contact-form textarea { min-height: 140px; resize: vertical; }
    .contact-form input::placeholder, .contact-form textarea::placeholder { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); }
    .btn-submit {
      align-self: flex-start; background: var(--gold); color: var(--navy);
      border: none; padding: 14px 32px;
      font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;
      cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
    }
    .btn-submit:hover { background: var(--gold-lt); transform: translateY(-2px); }

    /* ── FOOTER ── */
    footer {
      background: #070f1f; padding: 36px 80px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(201,151,0,0.15);
    }
    .footer-logo { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; color: var(--gold-lt); font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
    .footer-meta { font-size: 0.75rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); }
    .footer-nd { font-size: 0.75rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); }
    .footer-nd span { color: rgba(201,151,0,0.7); }

    /* ── FADE-IN ── */
    .fade-in { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(24px); transition: opacity 0.7s ease, transform 0.7s ease; }
    .fade-in.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }

    /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      #hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 100px 32px 60px; }
      .hero-photos { padding-left: 0; margin-top: 48px; grid-template-rows: 180px 180px; }
      section, #approach { padding: 72px 32px; }
      .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .about-card { max-width: 320px; }
      .approach-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .research-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .contact-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .photo-strip { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; height: auto; }
      .strip-photo { height: 200px; }
      .expertise-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      nav { padding: 0 24px; }
      .nav-links { gap: 18px; }
      footer { flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; text-align: center; padding: 28px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- NAV -->
  <nav>
    <a class="nav-logo" href="#hero">REACH Lab</a>
    <ul class="nav-links">
      <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="#research">Research</a></li>
      <li><a href="#publications">Publications</a></li>
      <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section id="hero">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <div class="hero-label">University of Notre Dame · Environmental Engineering</div>
      <div class="hero-acronym">REACH Lab</div>
      <p class="hero-mission">
        Increasing the effectiveness, adoption, and affordability of engineering technology
        in low- and middle-income countries to avert health and climate impacts.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Research on Energy, Air quality, Climate &amp; Health — combining rigorous quantitative methods
        with deep ethnographic fieldwork across East Africa and beyond.
      </p>
      <a href="#about" class="hero-cta">Meet the Lab</a>
      <a href="#contact" class="hero-cta-ghost">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-photos">
      <img class="tall" src="lpg_group.png" alt="Research team with LPG cylinders at community distribution event">
      <img src="WhatsApp_Image_2024-01-19_at_11_03_35.jpeg" alt="Lake Victoria shoreline with fishing boats">
      <img src="cooking_fieldwork.png" alt="Researcher cooking on traditional stove during fieldwork">
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT -->
  <section id="about">
    <div class="section-label">Principal Investigator</div>
    <h2>About</h2>
    <div class="about-grid fade-in">

      <div class="about-card">
        <img class="about-photo" src="headshot.png" alt="Principal Investigator">
        <div class="about-card-info">
          <div class="about-name">Annelise Gill-Wiehl</div>
          <div class="about-title-card">
            Assistant Professor<br>
            Civil &amp; Environmental Engineering &amp; Earth Sciences<br>
            University of Notre Dame
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-body">
        <div class="mission-block">
          <div class="mission-label">Mission</div>
          <div class="mission-text">
            Increasing the effectiveness, adoption, and affordability of technology
            in low- and middle-income countries to avert health and climate impacts.
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          I am an Assistant Professor of Environmental Engineering at the University of Notre Dame,
          where I lead the REACH Lab. My research sits at the intersection of energy access,
          air quality, and human health — with a focus on the billions of people who rely on
          solid biomass fuels for cooking and heating.
        </p>
        <p>
          What distinguishes our approach is the pairing of <strong style="color:var(--text);font-weight:500;">robust quantitative methods</strong> from
          biostatistics and impact evaluation with <strong style="color:var(--text);font-weight:500;">deep ethnographic qualitative work</strong>.
          I have conducted extensive fieldwork in East Africa, living and working alongside
          communities to understand how and why households make energy choices — and designing and testing
          interventions to increase their effectiveness, adoption, and affordability.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before joining Notre Dame, I was a postdoctoral researcher at Columbia University in Environmental Health Sciences. 
          I received by MS and PhD in Energy & Resources from UC Berkeley. I went to Notre Dame for my undergraduate degree 
          in Environmental Engineering. When I'm not working on energy access, I enjoy long distance running, walking my dog, Barkeley, 
          and hiking with my family.
        </p>

        <div class="expertise-grid">
          <div class="expertise-item">
            <div class="expertise-dot"></div>
            <div class="expertise-text">
              <strong>Experimental &amp; Quasi-Experimental Design</strong>
              Randomized trials and natural experiments to evaluate interventions
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="expertise-item">
            <div class="expertise-dot"></div>
            <div class="expertise-text">
              <strong>Observational Study Design</strong>
              Understanding drivers of energy choice and adoption and modeling the health and climate impacts of interventions
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="expertise-item">
            <div class="expertise-dot"></div>
            <div class="expertise-text">
              <strong>Field-Based Primary Data Collection</strong>
              Household surveys, stove use monitoring, and personal exposure measurement in LMICs
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="expertise-item">
            <div class="expertise-dot"></div>
            <div class="expertise-text">
              <strong>Qualitative Fieldwork</strong>
              In-depth interviews, focus groups, and ethnographic methods
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- APPROACH BAND -->
  <section id="approach">
    <div class="section-label">How We Work</div>
    <h2>Interdisciplinary Approach</h2>
    <div class="approach-grid fade-in">
      <div class="approach-text">
        <p>
          Understanding how to transition people to clean energy technologies requires
          more than engineering analysis alone. Our work bridges disciplines: we bring
          <strong>biostatistics and impact evaluation</strong> to bear on rigorous causal questions,
          while grounding our work in <strong>deep ethnographic understanding</strong> of the
          communities we work with.
        </p>
        <p>
          This means spending real time in the field — piloting surveys, sitting in homes conducting interviews and focus groups, talking with charcoal and gas sellers,
          talking with community members, and collecting personal exposure measurements. 
        </p>
        <p>
          Our fieldwork is largely based in East Africa (Tanzania and Kenya), but we also have projects working on affordability across the continent, 
          and we model the health and climate impacts of interventions at regional and global scales.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-methods">
        <div class="method-row">
          <span class="method-icon">🔬</span>
          <div>
            <div class="method-label">Randomized &amp; quasi-experimental trials</div>
            <div class="method-sub">Causal evaluation of technology interventions</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="method-row">
          <span class="method-icon">📋</span>
          <div>
            <div class="method-label">Field-based primary data collection</div>
            <div class="method-sub">Surveys, stove use monitoring, and personal exposure measurements</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="method-row">
          <span class="method-icon">🗣️</span>
          <div>
            <div class="method-label">Ethnographic qualitative fieldwork</div>
            <div class="method-sub">In-depth interviews, focus groups, participant observation</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="method-row">
          <span class="method-icon">🌍</span>
          <div>
            <div class="method-label">Emission reduction modeling</div>
            <div class="method-sub">National assessment of emission reductions from different policy pathways</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="method-row">
